              <span id="reviewTextContainer837927708" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1138842866133788493">Mesmerizing prose and thought provoking content, Three Lives is a masterwork of modernist fiction. Engaging with the limited syntactical toolbox that Stein employs is as much fun as coming to understand the arch of these three stories. The novel is a bonified classic. </span>

          </span>
